  abstract = {The interaction of the alpha-helical poly-L-lysine-heme complex with molecular oxygen, carbon monoxide, or cyanide ion was studied. Binding equilibrium curve and activation parameters for the reactions were determined. Sigmoid responses were observed for the absorption of molecular oxygen or carbon monoxide by the complex and the cooperative parameter was found to be 2.1. This indicated a cooperative interaction between hemes situated on a cylindrical alpha-helix of poly-L-lysine. But those of other polymer-ligand-heme complexes were 1.0. The cooperative reaction mechanism, in which an alpha-helical poly-L-lysine plays an important role, was suggested.},
